5:37:00','',0,'http://blog.jonvoth.com/?p=126',0,'post','',0),(268,2,'2010-01-23 11:43:17','2010-01-23 17:43:17','<a href=\"http://www.jonvoth.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/unofficial-google-wave-notifier.png\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-256\" style=\"margin: 10px;\" title=\"unofficial google wave notifier\" src=\"http://www.jonvoth.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/unofficial-google-wave-notifier-300x178.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"178\" /></a>If you\'re using Google Wave you\'re probably grappling with how to use it in your workflow, or trying to figure out how it could make communicating easier for you. This app is very useful in both cases...\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://blog.yakitara.com/2009/10/unofficial-google-wave-notifier-for-mac.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://blog.yakitara.com/2009/10/unofficial-google-wave-notifier-for-mac.html</a> (<a href=\"http://github.com/hiroshi/unofficial-Google-Wave-Notifier/downloads\" target=\"_blank\">Download Link</a>)\r\n\r\nIt\'s still quiteprimitive, but very functional. The app sits in your Mac\'s toolbar and lights up when you have new blips on a wave, displaying a number of total un-viewed blips. This simple functionality has allowed me to <em>actually</em> pay attention to Google Wave, turning Wave from a novelty into a tool.','Google Wave Notifier',0,'','inherit','open','open','','246-revision-7','','','2010-01-23 11:43:17','2010-01-23 17:43:17','',246,'http://www.jonvoth.com/2010/01/246-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(295,2,'2010-01-24 15:18:11','2010-01-24 21:18:11','<a href=\"http://www.jonvoth.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/tb_googaa.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-273\" title=\"Imagine That: Googaa Hunt\" src=\"http://www.jonvoth.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/tb_googaa.jpg\" alt=\"Imagine That: Googaa Hunt\" width=\"200\" height=\"130\" /></a>As the lead developer on this game for Nickelodeon and Paramount Pictures, I implemented a Flex application framework I had recently developed. After creating the core functionality I optimized the game\'s processor-intensive systems for improved performance.','Imagine That: Googaa Hunt Game',0,'Involvement: Development ','inherit','open','open','','95-revision-16','','','2010-01-24 15:18:11','2010-01-24 21:18:11','',95,'http://www.jonvoth.com/2010/01/95-revision-16/',0,'revision','',0),(286,2,'2010-01-23 11:47:36','2010-01-23 17:47:36','<a href=\"http://spongebob.nick.com/games/play/spongebob-gary/\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-106  alignnone\" title=\"Spongebob: Gary\'s Adventure Game\" src=\"http://jonvoth.com/content/tb_gary.jpg\" alt=\"Gary\'s Adventure\" /></a>\r\n\r\nIn this side-scrolling game for Nickelodeon\'s Spongebob franchise I developed several key systems including motion and physics, scoring and dynamic level layout.','Spongebob: Gary\'s Adventure Game',0,'Involvement: Development','inherit','open','open','','105-revision-10','','','2010-01-23 11:47:36','2010-01-23 17:47:36','',105,'http://www.jonvoth.com/2010/01/105-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(128,2,'2009-07-25 19:10:11','2009-07-26 01:10:11','[caption id=\"attachment_127\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"200\" caption=\"Click to view\"]<a href=\"http://www.larawyckoff.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-127 \" title=\"Lara Wyckoff Portfolio\" src=\"http://blog.jonvoth.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/tb_wyckoff.jpg\" alt=\"Click to view\" width=\"200\" height=\"143\" /></a>[/caption]\n\nInvolvement: Production, Development','Laura Wyckoff Protfolio',0,'Involvement: Production, Development','inherit','open','open','','126-revision','','','2009-07-25 19:10:11','2009-07-26 01:10:11','',126,'http://blog.jonvoth.com/?p=128',0,'revision','',0),(91,2,'2009-07-25 16:15:22','2009-07-25 22:15:22','Jon can be reached:\r\njonvoth@gmail.com\r\n<a style=\"text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer;\" href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/pub/2/793/959\" target=\"_blank\">LinkedIn &gt;&gt;</a>\r\n<a style=\"text