s/Flash/101507/HooverClean.aspx\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-110\" title=\"Hoover Clean Microsite\" src=\"http://blog.jonvoth.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/tb_hoover.jpg\" alt=\"Hoover Clean Microsite\" width=\"200\" height=\"138\" /></a>[/caption]\r\n\r\nThis microsite showcased demo animations of three Hoover vacuum models. I translated the designer\'s layout into a functional interface and constructed a system for connecting and looping FLV movies to display the demo animations.','Hoover Clean Microsite',0,'Involvement: Design, Production, Development','inherit','open','open','','109-revision-8','','','2009-11-26 00:18:31','2009-11-26 06:18:31','',109,'http://blog.jonvoth.com/2009/11/109-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),(234,2,'2009-11-26 00:17:13','2009-11-26 06:17:13','[caption id=\"attachment_106\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"200\" caption=\"Click to view\"]<a href=\"http://spongebob.nick.com/games/play/spongebob-gary/\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-106 \" title=\"Spongebob: Gary\'s Adventure Game\" src=\"http://blog.jonvoth.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/tb_gary.jpg\" alt=\"tb_gary\" width=\"200\" height=\"131\" /></a>[/caption]\r\n\r\nIn this side-scrolling game for Nickelodeon\'s Spongebob franchise I developed several key systems including motion and physics, scoring and dynamic level layout.','Spongebob: Gary\'s Adventure Game',0,'Involvement: Development','inherit','open','open','','105-revision-8','','','2009-11-26 00:17:13','2009-11-26 06:17:13','',105,'http://blog.jonvoth.com/2009/11/105-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),(235,2,'2009-10-18 19:54:34','2009-10-19 01:54:34','For my first Ham Jam (Ham\'s yearly soiree) I wanted to contribute to the party atmosphere. Since we had a DJ lined up, a dance floor, webcams, a slew of computers and we are an interactive shop, what could enhance the mood better than an motion-triggered interactive installation?\r\n\r\nAn external iSight webcam provides the video, a local SWF handles the logic and a projector displays the magic. The Actionscript used to accomplish this combines a few simple concepts:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Webcam - A WebCam class manages interaction between the Camera class and the rest of the app. The camera\'s video feed is passed into a Video object using the attachCamera() method.</li>\r\n	<li>BitmapData - The Video object\'s display is then drawn to a BitmapData object using the draw() method. For each frame of the camera\'s video feed this BitmapData object is merged with the previous frame\'s BitmapData using two filters: a color filter to highlight the pixels that have changed color value; and a blur filter to manage precision (and thus performance). The resulting image is then scanned, pixel by pixel, and pixels above a certain color threshold are recorded in a Point object and pushed into an array.</li>\r\n	<li>Particles - A particle is then created and placed at every Point in the array. The Particle object contains a display object and an update() method with logic that handles how the particle changes and animates over time.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe result is multiple swarms of particles emanating from your shadow as you move in front of the camera. You can check it out for yourself <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://dev.jonvoth.com/playground/HamJamDanceFloor/index.html\">here</a> if you have a webcam, or you can watch the video below. The quality isn\'t the best, but considering the lighting conditions it gets the point across:\r\n\r\n<object width=\"425\" height=\"344\"><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/jwaJCN-xuDQ&hl=en&fs=1&\"></param><param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\"></param><param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\"></param><embed src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/jwaJCN-xuDQ&hl=en&fs=1&\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" width=\"425\" height=\"344\"></embed></object>','Ham Jam Dance Floor Installation',0,'For my first Ham Jam (Ham\'s yearly soiree) I wanted to contribute to the party atmosphere. Since we had a DJ lined up, a dance floor, webcams, a slew of computers and we are an interactive shop, what could enhance the mood better than an motion-triggered interactive installation?','inherit','open','open','','139-revision-9','','','2009-10-18 19:54:34','2009-10-19 01:54:34','',139,'http://blog.jonvoth.com/2009/10/139-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(236,2,'2009-11-26 00:17:32','2009-11-26 06:17:32','[caption id=\"attachment_101\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"200\" caption=\"Click to view\"]<a href=\"http://www.spam.com/howto/game/default.aspx\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-101 \" title=\"SPAM\'s Break the Monotony Game\" src=\"http://blog.jonvoth.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/tb_spam.jpg\" alt=\"SPAM\" width=\"200\" height=\"131\" /></a>[/caption]\r\n\r\nThis game for Hormel\'s SPAM brand was built using skinned and custom Flex components. The ingredients and recipes are controlled from independent XML documents which allowed the client to refresh the game\'s content with minimal effort.','SPAM\'s Break the Monotony Game',0,'Involvement: Development','inherit','open','open','','100-revision-9','','','2009-11-26 00:17:32','2009-11-26 06:17:32','',100,'http://blog.jonvoth.com/2009/11/100-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(237,2,'2009-11-26 00:17:53','2009-11-26 06:17:53','[caption id=\"attachment_96\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"200\" caption=\"Click to view\"]<a title=\"Click to view\" href=\"http://jonvoth.com/content/portfolio/googaaHunt/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-96    \" title=\"Imagine That: Googaa Hunt Game\" src=\"http://blog.jonvoth.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/tb_googaa.jpg\" alt=\"Imagine That: Googaa Hunt Game\" width=\"200\" height=\"130\" /></a>[/caption]\r\n\r\nAs the lead developer on this game for Nickelodeon and Paramount Pictures, I implemented a Flex application framework I had recently developed.