target=\"LinkOut\">here</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n','MPLSArt iPhone App',0,'','inherit','open','open','','446-revision-10','','','2010-05-16 10:42:11','2010-05-16 16:42:11','',446,'http://www.jonvoth.com/uncategorized/446-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(458,2,'2010-05-16 10:14:49','2010-05-16 16:14:49','<img class=\"alignnone\" title=\"Fox-Deer Kiss\" src=\"http://img.visualizeus.com/thumbs/09/02/01/animals,deer,fox,kiss,so,cute-a34ebacfa855b69ad757bb8e24e2bcbf_h.jpg\" alt=\"Fox-Deer Kiss\" width=\"300\" />\r\n<p>A word to the wise; when including an external javascript file on an HTML page, always terminate your script tag with a closing script tag, not an inline closing slash.</p>\r\n<p>I ran into an issue where Firefox does not recognize that the script tag is closed and therefore does not render the remainder of your HTML code. This is quite a confusing issue when you specify your JavaScript include in the Head tag and end up with a completely plank render page in Firefox.</p>\r\n<p>Simply put, for Firefox compatibility use this:</p>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: monospace;\">&lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"/js/externalFile.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</span>\r\n<p>Not this:</p>\r\n<span style=\"font-family: monospace;\">&lt;script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"/js/externalFile.js\" /&gt;</span>','Making Firefox and Javascript play nice together',0,'','inherit','open','open','','438-revision-6','','','2010-05-16 10:14:49','2010-05-16 16:14:49','',438,'http://www.jonvoth.com/uncategorized/438-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(459,2,'2010-02-24 11:00:46','2010-02-24 17:00:46','<img src=\"http://www.jonvoth.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/jonBio.jpg\" style=\"float:left; margin-right:20px;\" />\r\n<p>If life gives you lemons, google \"how to make lemonade.\" </p>\r\n<p>After a BA in journalism, and a dip in the design world I landed on development. As it turns out, writing code provides a canvas that both my left and right brain can paint on. Along the way I have worked at a music distribution company, a branch of the UN, an advertising agency and a web design shop. </p>\r\n<p>All the while I\'ve found that the key to success on the web is understanding. Not only understanding the web as a medium but understanding your client\'s needs, your audience and the other members of your team. </p>\r\n<p>My skills include Flash & Flex development in AS3, CSS, HTML, JavaScript, PHP and XML. My interests include mobile app development, data & audio visualization, 3D engines and WordPress hackery.</p>\r\n<p>Clients I have shared success with: Adult Swim, Cargill, Cartoon Network, Hoover, Hormel Foods, Kelloggs, Marvin Windows, Nickelodeon, Paramount Pictures, Payless ShoeSource, Pfizer and Syngenta.</p>\r\n<p>Connect with me in the following ways:</p>\r\n<div><a href=\"mailto:jonvoth@gmail.com\" class=\"left rightMargin10\"><img src=\"/content/icon_gmail.jpg\" /></a><a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com/pub/2/793/959\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"left rightMargin10\"><img src=\"/content/icon_linkedin.jpg\" /></a><a href=\"http://www.behance.net/JonVoth\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"left rightMargin10\"><img src=\"/content/icon_behance.jpg\" /></a><a href=\"http://www.twitter.com/jonnyvoth\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"left rightMargin10\"><img src=\"/content/icon_twitter.jpg\" /></a></div>\r\n','About',0,'','inherit','open','open','','88-revision-35','','','2010-02-24 11:00:46','2010-02-24 17:00:46','',88,'http://www.jonvoth.com/uncategorized/88-revision-35/',0,'revision','',0),(460,2,'2010-07-01 18:03:56','2010-07-02 00:03:56','','work_adultSwim_fmtky3',0,'','inherit','open','open','','work_adultswim_fmtky3','','','2010-07-01 18:03:56','2010-07-02 00:03:56','',212,'http://www.jonvoth.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/07/work_adultSwim_fmtky3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(461,2,'2010-07-01 18:03:57','2010-07-02 00:03:57','','work_hoover_cleanMicrosite',0,'','inherit','open','open','','work_hoover_cleanmicrosite','','','2010-07-01 18:03:57','2010-