arently you must not only follow the \"@2x\" convention, but also explicitly specify paths to the various sizes of your App\'s icon files in a \"CFBundleIconFiles\" array.</p>\r\n<p>I found a great article at <a href=\"http://useyourloaf.com/blog/2010/8/4/application-icon-troubles.html\">Use Your Loaf</a> that helped resolve the issue. By specifying paths for each size of the app icon, the App Store error was resolved and we could also include icons at the correct sizes for all iOS device screens.</p>','iPhone App Icon Sizing Issues',0,'','inherit','open','open','','631-revision-8','','','2011-03-01 15:32:09','2011-03-01 21:32:09','',631,'http://www.jonvoth.com/uncategorized/631-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),(669,2,'2010-07-01 19:39:17','2010-07-02 01:39:17','<div style=\"float: left;\"><strong>Education</strong><br/>Bachelor of Arts, Journalism<br/><a href=\"http://umn.edu/\" target=\"_blank\">University of Minnesota</a> [<a href=\"http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;source=s_q&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=206+Church+Street+Southeast,+Minneapolis,+MN&amp;sll=44.975758,-93.23307&amp;sspn=0.020097,0.041842&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hq=&amp;hnear=206+Church+St+SE,+Minneapolis,+Hennepin,+Minnesota+55455&amp;ll=44.97547,-93.233864&amp;spn=0.010428,0.020921&amp;z=16&amp;iwloc=r2\" target=\"_blank\">Minneapolis, MN</a>]<br/>May 2004<br/><br/>\r\n<strong>Skills</strong><br/>- ActionScript 3<br/>- Objective C/iPhone Dev<br/>- HTML<br/>- CSS<br/>- JavaScript<br/>- XML<br/>- PHP<br/>- Adobe Creative Suite<br/>- Flex 3<br/><br/><strong>Interests</strong> <br/>- Mobile App Development<br/>- Data &amp; Audio Visualization<br/>- 3D Engines<br/>- WordPress Hackery<br/></div><div id=\"resumeRight\"><strong>Experience</strong><br/>Senior Developer<br/><a href=\"http://haminthefridge.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Ham in the Fridge</a> [<a href=\"http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;source=s_q&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=212+3rd+Ave+N,+Minneapolis,+MN+55401&amp;sll=44.977641,-93.270879&amp;sspn=0.